# Base userland for pocknix-os (Arch Linux ARM repos)
# One package per line; '#' comments and blank lines ignored.
# Phase 0 ships a minimal, bootable base. Session stacks live in their own lists.

# --- core system ---
base
systemd
systemd-sysvcompat
dbus-broker
mkinitcpio

# --- networking ---
networkmanager
iwd
wireless-regdb
openssh

# --- filesystem / storage ---
e2fsprogs
dosfstools
util-linux

# --- graphics stack (mesa from ALARM, NOT holo — see plan.md #1) ---
mesa
vulkan-freedreno
vulkan-icd-loader
libdrm
mesa-utils
vulkan-tools        # vulkaninfo + vkcube — confirm Turnip/GPU and test gamescope

# --- GPU firmware (Adreno 740) ---
# a740_sqe.fw + qcom/sm8550/a740_zap.mbn are NOT in the ROCKNIX overlay; they live
# in linux-firmware-qcom (shipped as .zst, so the kernel needs FW_LOADER_COMPRESS_ZSTD
# — enabled in build-kernel.sh). Required for Vulkan/GPU -> gamescope (Phase 3).
# (wifi/audio/video firmware still comes from the ROCKNIX overlay via install_firmware.)
linux-firmware-qcom

# --- audio ---
pipewire
pipewire-pulse
pipewire-alsa
wireplumber

# --- handheld input / quirks deps ---
# inputplumber config is shipped by pocknix-bsp (Phase 2); the daemon itself:
# inputplumber            # uncomment once available in repo/AUR build

# --- utilities ---
sudo
nano
less
htop
jq
zstd
